# AI Orchestrator ‚Äî MCP Tool Routing

You have access to MCP tools from the `ai-orchestrator` server. Use them instead of your built-in tools when the situation matches.

## Keyword triggers

When the user starts a message with these keywords, ALWAYS use the corresponding MCP tool:

- **"gemini, ..."** ‚Üí Route to the appropriate Gemini tool (`research`, `explain`, or `compare`) based on intent
- **"claude, ..."** ‚Üí Route to the appropriate Claude tool (`architect`, `implement`, `review`, `debug`, `test`, or `document`) based on intent
- **"research ..."** or **"deep dive ..."** or **"investigate ..."** ‚Üí `research`
- **"explain ..."** or **"what is ..."** or **"how does ... work"** ‚Üí `explain`
- **"compare ..."** or **"... vs ..."** or **"trade-offs ..."** ‚Üí `compare`
- **"plan ..."** or **"design ..."** or **"architect ..."** ‚Üí `architect`
- **"review ..."** or **"code review ..."** ‚Üí `review`
- **"debug ..."** or **"why is ... failing"** or **"root cause ..."** ‚Üí `debug`
- **"test ..."** or **"write tests for ..."** or **"generate tests ..."** ‚Üí `test`
- **"document ..."** or **"write docs for ..."** ‚Üí `document`
- **"orchestrate ..."** or **"deliberate ..."** ‚Üí `orchestrate`

## When to use MCP tools vs handle directly

For straightforward coding tasks (simple bug fixes, small features, renaming, formatting, adding fields), handle them yourself ‚Äî do NOT delegate to MCP tools. Only escalate when the task genuinely needs research, architecture, or is too complex for you.

When the user says "gemini" or "claude" explicitly, ALWAYS route to that model's tools ‚Äî never handle it yourself.

## Tool reference

### Gemini tools (research and analysis ‚Äî NOT for writing code)
- `research(question, context?)` ‚Äî deep domain/technology exploration
- `explain(code_or_concept, context?)` ‚Äî explain unfamiliar code or concepts
- `compare(option_a, option_b, context?)` ‚Äî trade-off analysis between options

### Claude tools (architecture, implementation, code quality ‚Äî full codebase access)
- `architect(goal, context?, constraints?)` ‚Äî design implementation plans
- `implement(spec, context?)` ‚Äî complex implementation
- `review(target, focus?)` ‚Äî thorough code review
- `debug(error, context?)` ‚Äî root cause analysis
- `test(target, context?)` ‚Äî generate test cases
- `document(target, style?)` ‚Äî generate documentation

### Orchestration (multi-model collaboration)
- `orchestrate(goal, context?)` ‚Äî Gemini researches + Claude architects in a back-and-forth deliberation loop, produces TASK.md
  - **IMPORTANT:** After orchestrate completes, show the user the TASK.md for review. Do NOT auto-implement. Wait for explicit user approval before running `implement`. Recommend committing current state as a checkpoint before implementation (`git add -A && git commit -m "checkpoint: before implementing TASK.md"`).

### Session management
- `new_session()` ‚Äî reset Claude + Gemini sessions for a fresh start
- `claude_usage()` ‚Äî token counts and costs
- `gemini_usage()` ‚Äî call counts for current session
